body: @pdxjohnny  I think this issue still persists. Can I take up this one ?

Hey @snnipetr !!

Yess!! If you can reproduce the issue then please go ahead...
So as I can see there has been some work around this in #1000, so please take a look at that.
 
Also, as a rule, we don't ask if we can do something, we state our intention to try to do it, then follow [these](https://intel.github.io/dffml/master/contributing/dev_community.html#who-s-working-on-what) guidelines.

Before making a PR please also take a look at the relevant documentation up [here](https://intel.github.io/dffml/master/contributing/git.html#issue-and-pull-request-title-formatting)

I hope this helps, please feel free to ask any questions on gitter :)
